   "source": [
    "# SchlierenCheckerboard Demo"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from skimage.io import imread\n",
    "from skimage.util import img_as_float\n",
    "\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "sys.path.insert(1, '../../')\n",
    "import schlieren_checkerboard as sc"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Parameters of the experiment and images (these are actually the default parameters) :"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pixmm = 0.025\n",
    "sqmm  = 0.5\n",
    "h     = 10\n",
    "alpha = 0.24"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Analyze a single image\n",
    "\n",
    "First load the image and create the deformed checkerboard object"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "img_file = 'images/image18.tif'\n",
    "img = img_as_float(imread(img_file, as_gray=True))\n",
    "dcf = sc.DeformedCheckerboard(img)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Then detect the corners and display"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "detect_corners: 126 corners detected\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "min_distance=8 #these are the default parameters\n",
    "window_size=13\n",
    "dcf.detect_corners(min_distance=min_distance, window_size=window_size)\n",
    "\n",
    "dcf.plot_corners()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Identify the center region where the lattice is not too deformed (meaning that the curvature is roughly constant)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dcf.center = [3.4, 4., 1.5]\n",
    "dcf.plot_corners()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Then match the corners to a lattice. The central point (closest to the defined center) and its nearest neighbor are used to determine the basis. Of course, the lattice matching is completely off when the deformation is large."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dcf.lattice_matching()\n",
    "dcf.plot_lattice_matching()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Compute the displacement of the corners, deduce the gradient with Schlieren formula  [Moisy et al. *Exp Fluids* (2009) 46:1021–1036], and fit to a gradient of constant curvature for the center region to get the curvature."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Curvature in the center:  0.07555093421747393 /mm\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dcf.disp_from_lm_corners()\n",
    "dcf.grad_from_disp()\n",
    "dcf.compute_center_curv()\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Curvature in the center: ', dcf.center_curv[0], '/mm')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Warning:** Since the lattice matching is completely off out of the center region, the displacement is wrong and so are all the quantities computed from it.\n",
    "\n",
    "Below we show the full displacement field."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dcf.plot_disp()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Analyze a sequence of images using corner tracking"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First load the images"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "img_files = ['images/image{:02d}.tif'.format(i) for i in range(1, 19)]\n",
    "img_list = [img_as_float(imread(img_file, as_gray=True)) for img_file in img_files]\n",
    "dc_list = [sc.DeformedCheckerboard(img) for img in img_list]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Then detect the corners"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "detect_corners: 145 corners detected\n",
      "detect_corners: 143 corners detected\n",
      "detect_corners: 141 corners detected\n",
      "detect_corners: 140 corners detected\n",
      "detect_corners: 136 corners detected\n",
      "detect_corners: 133 corners detected\n",
      "detect_corners: 126 corners detected\n",
      "detect_corners: 126 corners detected\n",
      "detect_corners: 123 corners detected\n",
      "detect_corners: 120 corners detected\n",
      "detect_corners: 121 corners detected\n",
      "detect_corners: 120 corners detected\n",
      "detect_corners: 121 corners detected\n",
      "detect_corners: 124 corners detected\n",
      "detect_corners: 125 corners detected\n",
      "detect_corners: 127 corners detected\n",
      "detect_corners: 129 corners detected\n",
      "detect_corners: 126 corners detected\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "min_distance=8 #these are the default parameters\n",
    "window_size=13\n",
    "\n",
    "for dc in dc_list :\n",
    "    dc.detect_corners(min_distance=min_distance, window_size=window_size)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "As can be seen, the curvature in the first image is almost constant and all the corners can be mapped on a square lattice. Here the center is not defined, so the corner closest to the center of mass of the detected corners is used."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dc_list[0].lattice_matching()\n",
    "dc_list[0].plot_lattice_matching()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Then we can track the corners between the following images in order to attribute a lattice point to every corner on all the images. This allows to get the displacement for all images."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "lattice_matching_tracking: 143 matches found\n",
      "lattice_matching_tracking: 141 matches found\n",
      "lattice_matching_tracking: 139 matches found\n",
      "lattice_matching_tracking: 135 matches found\n",
      "lattice_matching_tracking: 132 matches found\n",
      "lattice_matching_tracking: 125 matches found\n",
      "lattice_matching_tracking: 125 matches found\n",
      "lattice_matching_tracking: 121 matches found\n",
      "lattice_matching_tracking: 118 matches found\n",
      "lattice_matching_tracking: 117 matches found\n",
      "lattice_matching_tracking: 116 matches found\n",
      "lattice_matching_tracking: 114 matches found\n",
      "lattice_matching_tracking: 113 matches found\n",
      "lattice_matching_tracking: 113 matches found\n",
      "lattice_matching_tracking: 112 matches found\n",
      "lattice_matching_tracking: 111 matches found\n",
      "lattice_matching_tracking: 107 matches found\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "for i, dc in enumerate(dc_list[1:]) :\n",
    "    dc.lattice_matching_tracking(dc_list[i])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now the displacement and the gradient field can be computed. Interpolating the gradient field, we have access to the curvature. Note that the curvature is by default calculated only in the convex hull of the detected corners."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x576 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "for dc in dc_list :\n",
    "    dc.disp_from_lm_corners()\n",
    "    dc.grad_from_disp()\n",
    "    dc.curv_from_grad()\n",
    "    \n",
    "dc_list[-1].plot_curvature()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Approximating the curvature field as axisymmetric, we can get its axisymmetric approximation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "axisymmetry center: [3.3639462379028777, 4.113280015539842]\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 864x432 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dc_list[-1].axisym_curv(n=30, xguess=3.5, yguess=4., optimize=True)\n",
    "dc_list[-1].plot_axisym_curv()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Note the difference between the (wrong) displacement obtained before by direct lattice matching (top graph below) to the right displacement obtained with lattice tracking (bottom graph)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",

      "image/png": "\n",

       "<Figure size 576x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dcf.plot_disp()\n",
    "dc_list[-1].plot_disp()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Alternatively, we can plot the gradient field in polar coordinates around the center found previously. To do that, we have to shift the gradient by a constant vector for the gradient to be zero at the center; we have this freedom since there is an arbitrary component in the gradient, which is set by the reference point that we choose.\n",
    "\n",
    "The left panel below shows the shifted gradient field with the given center (red circle). The right panel shows the radial (filled circles) and azimuthal (open circles) components of the gradient as a function of the distance to the center."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 864x432 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dc_list[-1].polar_proj_grad(*dc_list[-1].axicurv[0])\n",
    "dc_list[-1].plot_polar_proj_grad()"
   ]
